Refresh pod git remotes after tunnel reconnect

Keep pod-side gateway URLs in sync when the daemon restarts and the
replacement tunnel binds a different in-container port. The tunnel
server notifies container-serve when it can, container-serve refreshes
git remotes on startup and before recovery pushes, and the regression
test forces a port change before `git push rumpelpod`.

The refresh skips .gitmodules entries whose submodule was never
initialized: git commands run in their empty placeholder directories
resolve to the parent repo and would rewrite its remotes.
